{
  "texts": [
    "Delivery Literacy Programs can introduce curriculum or workshops at universities and workplaces that promote informed delivery usage.",
    "Besides, Community-Based Sharing can encourage social platforms or peer groups to share meal experiences, reviews, and health tips to build collective awareness.",
    "Researchers can conduct longitudinal studies to assess causality between delivery usage and health impacts; compare results across multiple cities and income groups to understand regional variations.",
    "Moreover, neuro-marketing or biometric tools can better capture subconscious decision processes.",
